# =============================================================================
# üìù NOTES FOR DEVELOPERS
# =============================================================================
#
# IMPORTANT REMINDERS:
# 1. NEVER commit real secrets, even temporarily
# 2. Use AWS Secrets Manager / Parameter Store for all secrets
# 3. Use environment variables with proper defaults
# 4. Regularly audit git history for accidentally committed secrets
# 5. Consider using git-secrets or similar tools
#
# To check for secrets in existing commits:
# git log --oneline -S "password" --all
# git log --oneline -S "secret" --all 
# git log --oneline -S "key" --all
#
# To remove secrets from git history:
# git filter-branch --force --index-filter 'git rm --cached --ignore-unmatch .env' --prune-empty --tag-name-filter cat -- --all
# OR use BFG Repo-Cleaner (faster): 
# bfg --delete-files .env --delete-files db_creds.txt
#
# =============================================================================